subSubSection.paragraph:
The name is a Latin noun in apposition (
uncus
), meaning hook, and refers to the hook-like lamina medialis of gonopod.

Colour (Figure 27
A-E
). Specimens in life with body black; paraterga yellow/whitish yellow; head, antennae (except whitish distal part of antennomeres 7 and 8) and prozona black; collum, metaterga and surface below paraterga black/brownish black; sterna and epiproct brown; legs yellow; a few basal podomeres white.
